âœ… P4: Transaction Dataset Analysis

Sure-Shot Theory:

Pandas provides powerful tools for filtering, grouping, and aggregating data.
New columns can be derived from existing data using vectorized operations.
GroupBy and pivot tables help summarize sales performance and analyze customer behavior efficiently.




import pandas as pd

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Transaction.csv")

# 1. Filtering data
filtered = df[(df['payment_method'] == 'Credit Card') &
              (df['region'].isin(['North', 'South']))]

print("Filtered Data:\n", filtered)

# 2. New columns
df['total_sales'] = df['quantity_sold'] * df['price_per_unit']
df['discounted_sales'] = df['total_sales'] * 0.9

print("Discounted Sales > 400:\n", df[df['discounted_sales'] > 400])

# 3. Grouping & aggregation
grouped = df.groupby('product_name').agg({
    'quantity_sold': 'sum',
    'total_sales': 'sum'
})

print("Grouped Data:\n", grouped)

# 4. Handling missing & duplicate data
df.drop_duplicates(subset='transaction_id', inplace=True)
df['payment_method'].fillna('Unknown', inplace=True)
df = df[df['quantity_sold'] > 0]

# 5. Pivot table
df['month'] = pd.to_datetime(df['transaction_date']).dt.month

pivot = pd.pivot_table(df,
                       values='quantity_sold',
                       index='product_name',
                       columns='month',
                       aggfunc='sum',
                       fill_value=0)

pivot['Total'] = pivot.sum(axis=1)




ðŸŽ¤ Viva One-Liners

Why filtering? â†’ To select required data

Why groupby? â†’ To summarize data

Why pivot table? â†’ To reshape data

Why fillna? â†’ To handle missing values
print("Pivot Table:\n", pivot)
